WEBVTT

00:02.850 --> 00:05.473
you're listening to a teaching from Reality LA.

00:08.698 --> 00:17.950
I'll be preaching today on Matthew chapter 1, verses 18 through 25, and I've titled this sermon, God's relentless desire to dwell with his people.

00:19.091 --> 00:21.514
And as you turn to Matthew 1, let me tell you a quick story.

00:21.554 --> 00:27.442
This is in 1916, there was an explorer named Ernest Shackleton,

00:27.650 --> 00:36.162
whose ship going to Antarctica was crushed by ice, its sank, and it left him and his crew alone in Antarctica.

00:36.763 --> 00:52.344
And after months of starvation and freezing temperatures but still surviving, Shackleton left the crew and sailed 800 miles in a lifeboat across the most dangerous ocean on Earth so that he could come back for his men.

00:53.085 --> 00:56.530
He made it through storms, ice, and exhaustion.

00:56.642 --> 01:00.788
And when he finally reached them, the first thing he said was, are you all here?

01:00.848 --> 01:04.873
He refused to leave a single one behind.

01:05.554 --> 01:07.256
And that's what love does.

01:07.697 --> 01:09.059
Love doesn't abandon.

01:09.539 --> 01:10.821
Love doesn't stay safe.

01:10.961 --> 01:15.347
Love crosses impossible distances to be with the one it loves.

01:16.228 --> 01:20.594
And Christmas tells us that God went even further.

01:21.475 --> 01:26.482
And what we're going to see in Matthew chapter one is that God feels that way about us.

01:26.626 --> 01:28.849
Distance was not acceptable.

01:29.129 --> 01:31.271
Separation was not the end of the story.

01:31.752 --> 01:34.775
So God came to be with us.

01:35.856 --> 01:43.966
Let me read to you Matthew chapter one, verses 18 through 25, the Christmas story of how God came to be with us.

01:44.246 --> 01:47.750
And then I'll pray that God would speak to us through this story.

01:48.711 --> 01:50.453
Matthew one starting in verse 18.

01:51.955 --> 01:55.058
Now the birth of Jesus Christ took place in this way.

01:55.298 --> 02:01.966
When his mother Mary had been betrothed to Joseph, before they came together, she was found to be with child from the Holy Spirit.

02:02.647 --> 02:08.634
And her husband Joseph, being a just man and unwilling to put her to shame, resolved to divorce her quietly.

02:09.395 --> 02:22.450
But as he considered these things, behold, an angel of the Lord appeared to him in a dream saying, Joseph, son of David, do not fear to take Mary as your wife, for that which is conceived in her is from the Holy Spirit.

02:22.946 --> 02:28.414
She will bear a son, and you shall call his name Jesus, for he will save his people from their sins.

02:29.315 --> 02:32.419
All this took place to fulfill what the Lord had spoken by the prophet.

02:32.880 --> 02:41.131
Behold, the virgin shall conceive and bear a son, and they shall call his name Immanuel, which means God with us.

02:42.233 --> 02:45.938
When Joseph woke from sleep, he did as the angel of the Lord commanded him.

02:46.114 --> 02:52.760
He took his wife, but he knew her not until she had given birth to his son, and he called his name Jesus.

02:53.521 --> 02:55.143
This is God's word, pray with me.

02:56.944 --> 03:13.080
God, we pray this morning that you would slow down our hearts and focus our minds on the simple but beautiful truth that you have come to us in your son Jesus Christ and that you are with us.

03:14.461 --> 03:15.442
God, we pray that

03:16.130 --> 03:26.300
through this time that we would learn to relate to you, not based on our merit, our performance, but by your grace.

03:27.020 --> 03:33.506
You are a gracious God, merciful, abounding in steadfast love and faithfulness.

03:34.427 --> 03:46.098
And Lord, I pray this morning for those who are here who don't know you as Savior, I pray that you would reveal yourself to them this morning, that they wouldn't just go through a Christmas service,

03:46.338 --> 03:49.043
but they would have an encounter with the living Christ.

03:50.025 --> 03:59.963
And I pray for all of us, no matter what we're going through, no matter what we're carrying right now in this season, that we would know that you are with us and that that's enough.

04:00.705 --> 04:04.451
We pray this in Jesus' name, amen, amen.

04:05.453 --> 04:10.162
Well, the birth of Christ is a simple but powerful story.

04:10.946 --> 04:18.199
And yet what we have here in Matthew chapter 1 is not a picturesque nativity scene where the stable smells like a candle from target.

04:18.720 --> 04:22.967
Everyone is softly backlit and the animals are strangely well behaved.

04:23.869 --> 04:31.442
No, this was a messy, scandalous scene full of confusion, fear, and the very risk of real shame.

04:32.066 --> 04:34.309
You see, Mary and Joseph were betrothed.

04:34.509 --> 04:42.239
That means that they were legally pledged to be married, bound to one another in every way that mattered in the world, and yet the marriage had not yet been consummated.

04:42.940 --> 04:47.245
And then Mary is found to be pregnant.

04:47.265 --> 04:49.188
Now this wasn't sweet or sentimental.

04:49.288 --> 04:50.049
It was shocking.

04:50.830 --> 04:55.275
It was a moment of shame, crisis, and deep personal pain.

04:55.936 --> 04:57.298
And yet, right there,

04:57.666 --> 05:03.456
In the middle of what looks like a disaster, they encounter grace in the most unexpected way.

05:04.357 --> 05:09.987
The angel appears and says, don't be afraid for this is from the Holy Spirit.

05:10.448 --> 05:18.642
And then in verse 21, the angel declares, she will bear a son and you shall call his name Jesus, for he will save his people from their sins.

05:19.234 --> 05:27.623
In other words, this child is the Savior King, the one who will rescue us from our sin and renew all of creation.

05:28.664 --> 05:32.128
But this wasn't a random event or a last second decision by God.

05:32.789 --> 05:37.974
It was the fulfillment of a promise spoken hundreds of years earlier by the prophet Isaiah.

05:38.815 --> 05:44.882
He said, the virgin shall conceive and bear a son and they shall call his name Emmanuel.

05:45.378 --> 05:53.329
This child is the promised Savior, the one who will remove our shame, defeat evil, and fulfill all of our longings.

05:53.629 --> 05:57.114
He is the one who can truly bring peace on earth.

05:58.395 --> 06:09.490
But the key phrase that I want to slow down and sit with today is when the angel says they shall call his name Immanuel, which means God with us.

06:10.178 --> 06:10.999
It's amazing.

06:11.019 --> 06:16.044
I mean, this is one of the most powerful combinations of three words that you will ever hear in your life.

06:16.945 --> 06:20.748
And every single one of those words is exploding with meaning.

06:20.768 --> 06:25.173
And together these words communicate an idea that can change your life.

06:26.034 --> 06:31.119
Jesus is Immanuel, God with us.

06:33.101 --> 06:38.546
And so I want to invite you to slow down with me and reflect on this name of Jesus Immanuel.

06:38.914 --> 06:41.418
and explore the depth of each word.

06:42.280 --> 06:44.584
And so first, who is this child?

06:45.105 --> 06:48.311
He is God with us.

06:49.914 --> 06:58.269
If you think about it, most people across all cultures and generations believe in some kind of God or deity or higher power.

06:58.309 --> 07:01.234
For Plato, it was the unmoved mover.

07:01.538 --> 07:04.881
For someone like Oprah, it's the energy of the universe.

07:05.262 --> 07:08.745
For many young people today, the divine isn't out there.

07:08.765 --> 07:12.349
It's in here that self becomes sacred.

07:13.050 --> 07:16.253
But most people believe in the divine at some level.

07:17.154 --> 07:21.579
And yet, the Christmas story tells us something radically different.

07:21.599 --> 07:28.786
It tells us that this vulnerable, helpless infant lying in a manger is God himself.

07:29.410 --> 07:39.964
Not that a baby somehow became God, but that the eternal Son who has always existed stepped into our broken world as a man to bring healing and hope.

07:40.685 --> 07:42.248
And this is mind-blowing.

07:42.848 --> 07:45.892
It means that the king of the world came as a servant.

07:46.373 --> 07:49.257
The infinite became an infant.

07:49.858 --> 07:54.324
The one who holds the universe together allowed himself to be held.

07:54.364 --> 07:58.770
The God who fills the heavens, made himself small enough.

07:58.850 --> 08:01.033
to fit in the nook of Mary's elbow.

08:01.073 --> 08:04.598
And so what does this tell us about God?

08:05.579 --> 08:11.728
Well, people across cultures and across centuries have always wondered, what is God like?

08:12.469 --> 08:14.372
Christmas gives us an answer.

08:14.412 --> 08:16.975
It's not an abstract idea, but a person.

08:17.536 --> 08:19.679
God is like Jesus.

08:20.701 --> 08:25.567
And when we look at Jesus, we discover that God is not distant or detached.

08:26.268 --> 08:27.410
He's compassionate.

08:27.746 --> 08:32.573
He's sacrificial, He's present, and above all, He's loving.

08:32.613 --> 08:34.435
He's loving.

08:34.495 --> 08:43.288
That's why God would come in such a humble way because He didn't come merely to fix something that's broken or correct something that's out of line.

08:43.708 --> 08:47.574
He came because when He thinks about you, He's moved by love.

08:48.315 --> 08:50.237
He's overwhelmed with compassion.

08:50.298 --> 08:53.522
He's driven by mercy for you.

08:54.978 --> 09:04.910
That's the kind of God that Christmas reveals, a God who comes close, a God who enters into the mess, a God of self-giving love.

09:05.691 --> 09:06.192
Think about it.

09:06.752 --> 09:11.138
God did not come with a legion of soldiers or a display of overwhelming power.

09:11.178 --> 09:15.543
He didn't come as a conqueror, a philosopher, or a political ruler.

09:15.603 --> 09:22.211
He came as an infant, born to an unwed teenage girl in a town that anyone had hardly heard of.

09:22.652 --> 09:24.274
He came in love.

09:24.386 --> 09:26.268
That's what God is like.

09:27.289 --> 09:28.490
And that changes everything.

09:29.531 --> 09:36.358
This may seem obvious, but if you pull God out of this story, it's just another birth story.

09:37.179 --> 09:39.601
And the same is true of spirituality in general.

09:39.701 --> 09:46.488
If you pull God out of it, you're left with empty rituals, unkept promises, and religious buildings.

09:47.389 --> 09:52.754
It may look impressive on the outside, but it lacks the power to heal what's broken inside.

09:53.666 --> 09:56.589
But the Christmas story refuses to let us do that.

09:57.290 --> 10:02.856
At the center of the story is not an idea, a moral example, or a vague spiritual feeling.

10:03.197 --> 10:06.040
It's God himself drawing near.

10:06.080 --> 10:09.684
And when God is present, it changes everything.

10:09.724 --> 10:11.546
Hope becomes real.

10:11.606 --> 10:18.994
And faith is no longer reaching up to God, but about receiving the God who has come down to us.

10:20.514 --> 10:23.957
And that leads us to the next word in this life-changing phrase.

10:24.558 --> 10:27.901
Jesus is God with us.

10:28.682 --> 10:30.503
With, what a powerful word.

10:31.124 --> 10:38.831
And I want us to reflect on this because I think for many people, they think about it primarily in terms of God over us.

10:39.432 --> 10:41.794
He's a king who reigns over all.

10:41.874 --> 10:43.716
He made us, God over us.

10:43.776 --> 10:45.458
And yes, of course, that's true.

10:45.498 --> 10:48.060
We celebrate the sovereignty of God.

10:48.140 --> 10:50.162
He is over us, but we can't stop there.

10:50.530 --> 10:54.455
And so some people will go moved from there to God for us.

10:55.256 --> 11:01.804
That he sent his son Jesus to die for our sins and to rise from the grave so that we could be redeemed.

11:01.884 --> 11:03.606
And again, yes and amen.

11:03.706 --> 11:05.188
God is for us.

11:05.949 --> 11:07.030
But we can't stop there.

11:07.991 --> 11:11.015
God, we have to praise God above us and God for us.

11:12.177 --> 11:14.680
But what we see in this story is God with us.

11:16.482 --> 11:18.584
This is our greatest good.

11:19.225 --> 11:19.826
In fact,

11:20.354 --> 11:24.901
He reigns over us and dies for us so that he could be with us.

11:26.083 --> 11:27.486
This is what it culminates in.

11:28.387 --> 11:34.076
God doesn't ultimately want something from you, like your obedience or your service.

11:34.437 --> 11:35.479
He wants you.

11:35.519 --> 11:36.761
He loves you.

11:37.182 --> 11:38.364
He cares about you.

11:38.424 --> 11:41.228
He longs to be with you.

11:41.248 --> 11:47.218
And this idea of God being with us is not a

11:47.586 --> 11:50.129
Random detail of the Christmas story.

11:50.349 --> 11:52.231
This is the storyline of the Bible.

11:53.372 --> 11:57.837
In Genesis three, God walks in the garden with Adam and Eve.

11:57.857 --> 12:03.383
In the Old Testament, the tabernacle was where God dwelt with his people in the wilderness.

12:03.944 --> 12:08.169
The temple is how God dwelt with his people in the promised land.

12:08.489 --> 12:13.554
And then the whole story culminates in Jesus, who is the true tabernacle, the true temple.

12:13.875 --> 12:16.818
He is Emmanuel, God with us.

12:17.154 --> 12:20.058
And then you get all the way to the end of the Bible in Revelation 21.

12:20.359 --> 12:26.888
And God declares that He will dwell with His people in the new creation.

12:26.908 --> 12:34.479
And so throughout the story of Scripture, we see God's relentless desire to dwell with His people.

12:35.380 --> 12:40.147
Nothing can stop Him from this, not sin, not the devil, not even death.

12:41.008 --> 12:42.610
And Christmas is the moment.

12:42.978 --> 12:46.884
When God's desire to dwell with his people finally steps into history.

12:47.425 --> 12:52.313
When God doesn't just promise his presence, but arrives in person.

12:54.276 --> 13:01.407
I remember a time when I was a kid and my family went out and I got separated from my parents in the midst of a crowd.

13:02.248 --> 13:05.553
And as soon as I was separated from my parents, I was lost.

13:05.674 --> 13:06.595
I felt anxious.

13:06.675 --> 13:07.416
I was afraid.

13:07.476 --> 13:08.778
I started freaking out.

13:08.999 --> 13:11.122
I didn't know where to go or what to do.

13:12.162 --> 13:13.283
But my dad found me.

13:13.924 --> 13:17.268
And as soon as I was with my dad, everything was fine.

13:17.908 --> 13:18.669
I felt calm.

13:18.689 --> 13:19.750
I felt at peace.

13:20.411 --> 13:21.272
I knew what we were doing.

13:21.312 --> 13:22.433
I knew where we were going.

13:23.374 --> 13:26.238
Well, without God, we're lost.

13:27.118 --> 13:28.800
And so, of course, we're gonna be afraid.

13:28.840 --> 13:29.821
We're gonna be anxious.

13:29.861 --> 13:30.562
We're not gonna go.

13:30.602 --> 13:34.286
We're not gonna know where we're going or what we're doing or who we are.

13:34.326 --> 13:38.111
And yet with God, we can have calm.

13:38.151 --> 13:39.873
We can have peace.

13:39.933 --> 13:41.234
I'm not saying it's easy.

13:42.050 --> 13:46.295
But we can have purpose because of God's presence in our lives.

13:47.276 --> 13:55.145
I think about what David said in Psalm 23, even though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil.

13:55.185 --> 13:55.466
Why?

13:55.966 --> 13:57.428
For you are with me.

13:57.468 --> 14:02.133
That's what brings us peace, even in the storm.

14:02.173 --> 14:06.258
That's what brings us calm, even amid the chaos.

14:06.754 --> 14:09.337
that God is with us.

14:09.518 --> 14:11.300
This is our greatest good.

14:11.440 --> 14:14.324
And this is what the story of Christmas is about.

14:14.825 --> 14:17.949
And it's all in this powerful word with.

14:22.275 --> 14:28.583
But I want to acknowledge that there are at least two ways of thinking about God that will prevent us from this.

14:28.623 --> 14:30.866
Because it sounds like a great idea, right?

14:31.202 --> 14:32.924
God wants to be with me.

14:33.004 --> 14:34.186
I want to be with God.

14:34.266 --> 14:42.356
But there's two ways of thinking about God that not only can, but actually do prevent a lot of people from experiencing God's presence in this way.

14:42.957 --> 14:47.803
And the first way is that that prevents this is when we think of God as a transactional God.

14:48.844 --> 14:53.209
And at this time of year, it's easy to explain what a transactional relationship looks like.

14:54.471 --> 14:56.153
He's making a list.

14:56.173 --> 14:57.254
He's checking it twice.

14:58.135 --> 15:00.178
He's going to find out who's naughty or nice.

15:00.738 --> 15:00.958
Right?

15:00.978 --> 15:03.862
I mean, this is how Santa works, right?

15:03.882 --> 15:06.465
Like, if you do good, you get more presents.

15:06.585 --> 15:08.567
If you don't, you get a lump of coal.

15:09.568 --> 15:15.616
And what's interesting is that nobody strives for a relationship with Santa.

15:15.636 --> 15:16.397
You ever notice that?

15:17.218 --> 15:20.802
Nobody's ever sitting around in March being like, we're Santa, I miss him.

15:20.822 --> 15:27.730
Like, no, like he just shows up once a year, drops off gifts, and then leaves and we wait for him later next year.

15:27.970 --> 15:35.300
And so when it comes to Santa, we like the gifts more than the giver, and we've kind of all accepted that that's okay, right?

15:36.161 --> 15:38.424
But here's the thing, God is not like that.

15:39.245 --> 15:43.951
He does not desire nor is he okay with a transactional relationship.

15:44.792 --> 15:49.799
So he gives gifts, yes, but it's not based on our merit.

15:49.879 --> 15:55.346
It's completely based on his grace, his unconditional love for you.

15:55.810 --> 16:02.378
And so our relationship with God is not dependent on our religious performance, but on His grace.

16:03.199 --> 16:04.160
He's gracious.

16:04.200 --> 16:05.382
That's who God is.

16:05.422 --> 16:07.044
He's not a transactional God.

16:07.885 --> 16:21.842
But not only does God give us gifts of grace, His greatest gift is that He gives us Himself so that we can know Him and be known by Him, so that we can love Him and be loved by Him.

16:22.018 --> 16:26.443
so that we can have a deep, loving, intimate relationship with Him.

16:26.483 --> 16:35.193
God is not like an absent dad who tries to buy his kid's love with gifts, but doesn't have time to be with them.

16:35.213 --> 16:45.104
No, God gives us many gifts, but what his heart beats for, what he loves most, is simply to be with us.

16:46.225 --> 16:47.947
He's not a transactional God.

16:48.568 --> 16:50.450
He's a relational God.

16:51.266 --> 16:53.509
That's why being with Him is our greatest good.

16:55.051 --> 17:02.101
And so having a transactional view of God will prevent us from experiencing the presence of God in this way.

17:02.141 --> 17:08.029
But the other thing, the second thing that will prevent us from this is viewing God as a distant God.

17:09.271 --> 17:14.138
I think many people believe in God, but they assume that He doesn't care.

17:14.178 --> 17:15.620
He's aloof.

17:15.941 --> 17:17.122
He doesn't understand.

17:17.182 --> 17:18.284
He's not involved.

17:18.304 --> 17:19.826
He's a distant God.

17:20.802 --> 17:22.825
But listen to what A.W.

17:22.865 --> 17:31.557
Tozer once said, the incarnation is a message to the world that God will not stay at a distance.

17:31.577 --> 17:32.318
He has come.

17:32.338 --> 17:33.820
He has drawn near.

17:33.880 --> 17:40.289
And once you know God with us, you can never believe in a distant God again.

17:40.330 --> 17:42.152
Isn't that beautiful?

17:42.953 --> 17:49.202
Once you see this, that God is with us and sending His Son, you can never believe in a distant God again.

17:49.666 --> 17:54.553
And brothers and sisters, let's not just think about this in theory.

17:55.334 --> 18:00.922
Whatever you are going through, whatever you are experiencing, God is with you.

18:00.962 --> 18:04.247
God is with you in your anxiety.

18:05.068 --> 18:07.071
God is with you in your depression.

18:07.792 --> 18:09.434
God is with you in your loneliness.

18:10.295 --> 18:12.338
God is with you in your relational tension.

18:12.438 --> 18:14.962
God is with you in your exhaustion.

18:15.266 --> 18:17.129
God is with you in your loss.

18:17.229 --> 18:19.292
God is with you in your suffering.

18:19.593 --> 18:21.616
God is with you in your physical pain.

18:21.676 --> 18:24.300
God is with you in your waiting.

18:24.340 --> 18:31.371
And if we ever forget that, we only need to look to Jesus who is Emmanuel, God with us.

18:32.373 --> 18:33.655
He's not a distant God.

18:34.316 --> 18:37.321
He's the God who has drawn near to us in love.

18:38.522 --> 18:39.604
So maybe we remember this.

18:39.624 --> 18:43.410
Our greatest good is not what we do for God.

18:43.842 --> 18:46.025
It's not even what we receive from God.

18:46.605 --> 18:49.729
Our greatest good is that we get to be with God.

18:51.471 --> 18:56.697
Now, we also need to reflect on the significance of this last two-letter word, us.

18:57.778 --> 18:58.839
God with us.

18:59.600 --> 19:03.565
There's so much grace in this one little word.

19:03.605 --> 19:08.050
And I want you to notice, it doesn't say God with me.

19:08.386 --> 19:10.688
It couldn't say that, and that would be true.

19:10.749 --> 19:11.770
That's amazing.

19:11.990 --> 19:15.133
But it says more than that, God with us.

19:16.435 --> 19:22.661
Christ came so that we would be reconciled to God and so that we would be adopted into His family.

19:23.903 --> 19:28.428
And that family, by the way, is not a bunch of perfect people who've got it all figured out.

19:29.409 --> 19:33.753
Now, just before this passage in Matthew 1 is the family line of Jesus.

19:34.614 --> 19:38.098
And what's included in that genealogy is a prostitute.

19:38.466 --> 19:45.615
a murderer, a thief, an adulterer, and many who are on the fringes of society.

19:46.516 --> 19:48.639
They're not good people who God rewarded.

19:48.659 --> 19:50.421
They're sinful people that God redeemed.

19:51.642 --> 20:00.894
And the family line of Jesus teaches us that Jesus came from sinners and outcasts and that Jesus came for sinners and outcasts.

20:01.975 --> 20:04.178
And so Christmas reminds us

20:05.154 --> 20:07.958
That Jesus didn't come for people who have it all together.

20:08.038 --> 20:13.586
He came for people who know that they're hurting, broken, overlooked, weary, and on the verge of giving up.

20:13.646 --> 20:15.449
I know that that's many of you here today.

20:15.809 --> 20:16.891
Jesus came for you.

20:16.931 --> 20:24.622
And the good news of Christmas is not only that God has come to us, but that in Him we have one another.

20:24.662 --> 20:27.346
God with us.

20:28.802 --> 20:35.050
Now, I'm so glad that we have a lot of our children in here with us today, but I also know that I've lost most of you at this point, okay?

20:35.411 --> 20:36.973
So kids, can I have your attention?

20:37.033 --> 20:40.578
Because I want to tell you about my favorite Christmas movie.

20:41.138 --> 20:45.444
Okay, my favorite Christmas movie is Home Alone, all right?

20:45.624 --> 20:48.428
Now, maybe all the little kids haven't seen it.

20:48.488 --> 20:52.754
You need to trust your parents if when is the age-appropriate time for you to watch that, all right?

20:52.834 --> 20:59.262
Let's just say that there's some sibling interactions that don't exactly represent Christ in the movie, okay?

20:59.322 --> 21:10.056
But when you watch it, you'll see that this is a movie about a kid whose parents go off to, or family goes off to vacation in France, and he gets left home alone.

21:10.537 --> 21:15.143
Now, of course, Kevin McAllister spends almost the entire movie alone.

21:15.243 --> 21:17.746
I mean, it's called home alone, but

21:18.050 --> 21:26.960
There is one scene where he enters into community and has a significant experience and that's when he enters into the church.

21:27.922 --> 21:28.742
You remember the scene?

21:28.762 --> 21:37.513
He walks into the church, he sees the color of the stained glass windows, the warmth of the candles, the cross lifted high above all.

21:38.394 --> 21:45.522
He sits down in an empty pew and then he hears the choir singing and all of a sudden it's beautiful, it's peaceful, he's calm,

21:45.922 --> 21:53.572
And then he notices across the aisle, an old man, a man that he assumed was scary, terrifying, maybe even dangerous.

21:54.433 --> 21:59.760
But then the man comes and begins to talk with him and he realizes that he's not frightening.

21:59.980 --> 22:00.942
He's lonely.

22:01.042 --> 22:04.126
He's a man who's been estranged from his own family.

22:04.907 --> 22:11.736
And they have this powerful conversation about fear and reconciliation and loving people through our pain.

22:11.796 --> 22:13.458
It's a heartwarming moment.

22:14.754 --> 22:21.602
And then, of course, it goes on to one of the greatest cinematic scenes of all time, where Kevin outwits and humiliates Harry and Marv in his own home.

22:23.103 --> 22:30.612
But at the end of the movie, the old man is reunited with his family on Christmas Day, and Kevin is reconciled with his family and their own home.

22:32.074 --> 22:43.186
And think about it, amid the whole movie about being alone, Kevin has this one positive communal experience, and it's in the church, a place marked by God's presence.

22:43.874 --> 22:52.063
And I tell that story because the church is meant to be the place where we run to endanger and find peace and solace.

22:52.083 --> 23:02.054
And God has called us not to individual spirituality, but to a communal, embodied faith where we experience God's redeeming grace together.

23:03.095 --> 23:07.399
The good news is not only that we're with God, but that we're with one another.

23:08.180 --> 23:13.426
God is with us.

23:13.666 --> 23:17.491
talked about these three words, God with us.

23:18.272 --> 23:22.698
But I want to close by talking about how much the order of these words matters.

23:23.979 --> 23:27.324
The message of the Bible is not us with God.

23:28.425 --> 23:30.548
We do not ascend to Him with works.

23:30.608 --> 23:33.071
That's what every other religion is ultimately about.

23:33.652 --> 23:35.875
We don't ascend to God in works.

23:35.895 --> 23:38.418
He descends to us in grace.

23:39.298 --> 23:40.820
We don't meet Him halfway.

23:41.160 --> 23:44.565
Christmas tells us that He came all the way in love for us.

23:45.406 --> 23:51.293
And that's why when we talk about love on Christmas, may we remember that we don't initiate love with God.

23:52.034 --> 23:55.779
We respond to His love that initiated with us.

23:55.799 --> 23:58.883
1 John 4 19 says it explicitly.

23:59.224 --> 24:02.568
We love because He first loved us.

24:04.090 --> 24:07.314
And this love isn't a nice holiday gesture.

24:07.682 --> 24:11.466
as if God's love would enhance our otherwise okay lives.

24:11.546 --> 24:18.373
No, God's love is absolutely necessary to get us out of this mess that we've got ourselves into.

24:18.413 --> 24:25.020
You see, the Bible says that because of our sin, that we are separated from God.

24:26.302 --> 24:28.064
We're separated from God because of our sin.

24:28.084 --> 24:29.025
We are not with God.

24:29.045 --> 24:30.486
We are separated from Him.

24:30.546 --> 24:33.970
But in love, Christ came for us.

24:34.562 --> 24:41.710
And Jesus is the mediator between a just God and a unholy, sinful people.

24:43.191 --> 24:54.743
And so he comes to us and we see in this story that he came to the lowest of lows, the most vulnerable place imaginable, but the story doesn't stop in the manger.

24:55.564 --> 25:01.010
Jesus went to the cross and it's there where we see the fullness of God's love for us.

25:01.634 --> 25:08.562
Romans 5.8 says, God demonstrates His love in this, that while we were still sinners, Christ died for us.

25:09.583 --> 25:18.813
He died in our place for our sin so that we could be forgiven, washed clean, reconciled to God, and given a new life.

25:19.574 --> 25:24.960
Only in Christ can we say, God is with us.

25:26.441 --> 25:29.485
But it doesn't even stop there after the manger and the cross.

25:29.525 --> 25:30.866
We have the empty tomb.

25:31.234 --> 25:43.293
Because on that Sunday, he got up, he rose from the grave, conquering sin, Satan, and death so that we can have eternal life and we can know that he is with us no matter what comes our way in this life.

25:44.454 --> 25:50.644
Jesus is Emmanuel, the one who came to be with us and to save us.

25:52.006 --> 25:57.034
And this salvation truly is the greatest gift of all.

25:58.256 --> 25:59.858
You know, in just a few days,

26:00.834 --> 26:03.817
we'll be able to open presence, to sit under the tree.

26:03.897 --> 26:09.344
Kids, you know the anticipation is building up your longing and that moment will come.

26:09.384 --> 26:10.885
I can see them smiling right now.

26:11.206 --> 26:17.733
That moment will come when you get to unwrap that present and you experience the joy of that gift.

26:19.054 --> 26:24.681
But what we read in scripture is that the greatest gift truly is the gift of salvation in Christ.

26:25.522 --> 26:29.426
It's not a momentary gift, it's an eternal gift.

26:29.762 --> 26:39.073
It's not something that you will ever grow tired of or move on from, but that you will go deeper into its riches, the rest of your life, and for all of eternity.

26:39.954 --> 26:43.858
And I want you to listen to what Ephesians chapter two says about how we receive that gift.

26:43.918 --> 26:49.144
Ephesians two eight says, for by grace you have been saved through faith.

26:49.825 --> 26:52.188
And this is not your own doing, it is the gift of God.

26:52.228 --> 26:53.709
So salvation is a gift.

26:54.290 --> 26:55.191
It's not deserved.

26:56.553 --> 26:57.874
You can't earn it.

26:58.306 --> 27:01.329
It's just because God is abounding and mercy and love for you.

27:02.130 --> 27:05.694
And yet, how do we receive a gift with open hands?

27:06.314 --> 27:10.639
We open it up and we receive it with joy and with gratitude.

27:11.399 --> 27:12.300
That's what faith is.

27:12.320 --> 27:25.714
It's letting go of the grip of our own lives, opening up to receive the gift of God's grace, with joy and with gratitude, and then with a response that says, my life is yours.

27:26.146 --> 27:33.056
I want to live the life of joy and gratitude and worship because of what God has done for me in Christ.

27:33.657 --> 27:34.598
That's the good news.

27:35.840 --> 27:47.456
And so this Christmas, whatever you're carrying, whatever you're walking through, may you remember there is hope, there is peace, there is joy because Christ has come.

27:47.496 --> 27:50.701
And that means that God is with us.

27:51.342 --> 27:51.822
Pray with me.

27:53.104 --> 27:54.546
God, we thank you so much.

27:55.298 --> 28:03.587
that your response to our sin, to our own brokenness is to draw near to us.

28:05.049 --> 28:20.786
And that you've done that, Lord, in the most tangible way possible, in sending your son in the flesh who became a vulnerable infant for us, who lived a perfect life.

28:20.866 --> 28:27.212
for us, who died for us, who rose for us, and who reigns on high for us.

28:28.293 --> 28:32.117
And so, God, we pray that you would give us the faith to receive of your grace.

28:33.098 --> 28:39.444
And God made the joy well up in our hearts, seeing who you are and what you've done for us.

28:40.004 --> 28:44.669
We thank you that no matter what comes our way and that because of Christ, we can know that you are with us.

28:45.229 --> 28:46.330
We pray this in His name.

28:46.711 --> 28:47.031
Amen.

28:48.933 --> 28:49.033
Amen.

28:49.053 --> 28:50.034
Thank you for listening.

28:50.402 --> 28:54.738
For more audio and video content, please visit realityla.com.

